					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>The inscription is damaged. It seems to record a sale of some land irrigated by the local tank, by the <hi rend="italic">mahāsabhā</hi> of Kiḷinallūr in Ōymā-nāḍu to <hi rend="bold">Śāttaṉ Mallaḍigaḷ of Pākkam</hi> in Vēśālippāḍi with the condition that he was to contribute a <hi rend="italic">tūṇi</hi> of paddy after every harvest towards (the maintenance of) <hi rend="bold">the tank</hi> besides paying the <hi rend="italic">maṉṟupāḍu</hi> (tax) due to the reigning king. This is assignable to <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḻa.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
